<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Lind:
[B] [QUOTE]Originally posted by Kero:
[b] Let me just say first off that this statement got my curiosity going.  To see the results, go to [URL=http://www.skybyrd.net/clericvsdruid.htm]http://www.skybyrd.net/clericvsdruid.htm[/URL] 

It seems to prove Lind wrong, but I'm welcome to criticism, if I did things wrong.  For percentage, it's "Percentage of (heal/damage) that (class) has."  If that made any sense at all.

Anyway, tell me what you think.[/b][/QUOTE]
 
  You're comparing damage per second and heals per second not efficiency which is much more important.  You also only compare divine light which is not a clerics best heal and not the only way even that a cleric can be tossing health per second.
 
  Even if CE or CH were only 4.4 health per mana (they're better) you'd still be healing 2 hps for every 1 a druid could.  With moonfire a druid will end up dealing like 1.5 damage for every 1 the cleric does.[/B][/QUOTE]

